PUNITIVE DAMAGES

"Punitive Damages: A State-By-State Guide to Law &
Practice" has been published by West Publishing Co. (St.
Paul, MN). The 500-page book shows how to recover or defend
against punitive damages in all 50 states. It discusses
conduct required for recovery, defenses, jury instructions,
tax consequences, insurability, reinsurance, and conflict
of law issues. It also analyzes a recent U.S. Supreme Court
case which upheld damages against constitutional
challanges. A bibliography lists damages by type of action.




