MANAGEMENT MATTERS via NewsNet
January 1996

THE ISO-9000 SERIES OF QUALITY STANDARDS

This report (from the Ei Compendex Plus Database)
covers about everything you may want to know about the
international ISO-9000 quality standards.  It covers
information and details of, for example: documentation
written by the Geneva-based International Standards
Organization; ISO implementation and registration
requirements adopted by the 12 European Economic
Community (EC) countries; certification of quality
systems on the basis of the ISO international standard;
internal and external auditing processes required for
registration; the benefits and competitive advantages
of receiving IS0-9000 certification; present case
studies of companies that have received certification;
and much more.  The report consists of a collection of
abstracts of available reports, papers, studies, and
other documentation, with references for their
acquisition and extensive indexing to make it easy to
find exactly what you want.  It will be updated to
include the most current information available at the
time you place your order.

(Order this MANAGEMENT MATTERS reviewed report from
InfoTeam Inc., P.O. Box 15640, Plantation, FL
33318-5640; Phone (954)/or(305) 473-9560, Fax
(954)/or(305) 473-0544: Report No. MD510H; latest 250
citations, updated to the date of your order.  Price:
$319.00, prepaid.)




