MANAGEMENT MATTERS via NewsNet
January 1996

SOFTWARE MEASUREMENT GUIDEBOOK

This software measurement guidebook (by the Software
Productivity Consortium) provides practical
quantitative support guidance for managing a software
project.  It shows how to apply the
goal-question-metric (GQM) paradigm in order to
systematically select metrics for purposes of project
control and/or process improvement.  The guidebook:
presents methods for estimating software size, cost,
and development schedule; presents methods for
monitoring and evaluating the status of a software
project; describes the role of software metrics in
raising the capability maturity level of a software
development organization; presents guidance on how to
collect and validate metrics data and how to feed back
experience data to developers as part of statistical
process control; presents measures of software quality;
describes models for estimating and predicting software
defects; gives methods for estimating the impact of
code reuse on software cost, schedule, and quality; and
more.

(Order this MANAGEMENT MATTERS reviewed report from
InfoTeam Inc., P.O. Box 15640, Plantation, FL
33318-5640; Phone (954)/or(305) 473-9560, Fax
(954)/or(305) 473-0544: Report No. M960109; Aug. 1993,
273 pp.  Price: $299.00, prepaid.)




