SMALL BUSINESS ENTREPRENEURSHIP IN THE 21ST CENTURY

As we enter the 21st century, will the social and
economic environment in the U.S. be favorable for small
business?  To answer the question, this (Small Business
Administration) report presents: (1) an executive
summary of the researchers' findings; (2) a report on
the insights garnered from a series of 15 focus groups
held in late 1994 and early 1995; and (3) a
presentation of the economic and demographic changes
that will affect small businesses in the next 10 years.

