MANAGEMENT POLICIES & PERSONNEL LAW via NewsNet
April 15, 1994

HOW MUCH DOES AN EMPLOYEE COST?

According to Chrysler Motors, the total
lifetime cost of a new worker is $7 million.
Dennis Pawley, Chrysler's head of
manufacturing, says that figure includes all
items associated with the hiring process:
background checks, hiring, remedial education,
salary, benefits and employee assistance
programs.



